node.text:
Legendary wrestler Ric Flair reportedly released by WWE. According to NY Post, The 16-time world champion was “frustrated” with recent booking decisions and contacted WWE chairman Vince McMahon directly to share his frustration and request his release.
He reportedly got his wish.

Earlier in the year, “The Nature Boy” was in a storyline with his daughter, Charlotte Flair, and Lacey Evans, but it was dropped when Evans became pregnant in real life.

Ric Flair, 72, was unhappy with his role – there was a slight romantic angle brewing in the storyline with Evans, who is more than 40 years younger than Flair and married – and shared this with McMahon.
